  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Sarah Hussey Earle introduces her abolitionist friend, Elizabeth Southwick of Leicester, who is going to Boston to attend the anti-slavery fair and would like to make herself useful. Sarah H. Earle has been put in charge of the anti-slavery contributions from Worcester, which are listed on page three of this manuscript. Earle comments: &quot;The prices attached to these articles are not like the Laws of the Medes &amp; Persians.&quot;</subfield>
